<span class="name"><a name="31549"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#17:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>What a hoot.</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>turgeon</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=31549&amp;sid=5548bb692cb00b258589e6b729c54a60#31549"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Tue Feb 04, 2003 10:03 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
	<span class="gensmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;----</span><br>

<span class="postbody">Finished this quest last night and boy was it a blast.  
<br />
The party:  49 Beastlord (me) & 52 Cat Bard
<br />
Prep:  I showed my buddy the area we would be fighting and gave him the name of the scout and told him the goal was a grimling officer.  He setup his hotkeys.  I setup 2 hotkeys.  The first was the /assist Scout Husman with /pet attack  and the other /pet attact A grimling Officer.
<br />

<br />
The start: I put on my CHR gear and purchased the sphere for 55 plat and some change.  Gave it to the scout.  It took him a bit to get moving and even longer to get to the camp.
<br />

<br />
The battles: The scout charges the camp and we start the game of "keep the grimling away from the scout".  I made sure that I took off autoattack before switching targets as to not accidently attack Husman.  
<br />

<br />
The battles keep comming:  Wave after wave of grimlings came and no officer.  I would always hit my /pet attack a grimling officer key during the fight to see if the pet keyed upon the presence of the officer.  After the 7th wave of grimlings the pet ran off and engaged the officer (lt blue con to 49) and soloed him save the one kick i got in.
<br />

<br />
I looted the scalp, a mangy mantle, and some other no drop gear, some junk claws and a note.  I gave the note to the scout at the end of the battle and recieved the medal.
<br />

<br />
The quest was a ton of fun.  The time did go by fast, although I do know we were there over an hour, as SOW wore off twice.  
<br />

<br />
My bard buddy said, upon completion of the quest, "too bad you only have to do this once, that was a total blast."  I agree.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
